════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
MISSION — polylogue-rxdo.4: AssertionKind.FINDING
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
A finding is a durable CLAIM WITH EVIDENCE — (n, statistic, query_ref,
result_set_ref, expected) — produced by a detector/agent/analysis, stored
as an assertion row so the ENTIRE existing lifecycle is reused with zero
new lifecycle code: candidate default → judge_assertion_candidate
accept/reject/defer/supersede → judgment recorded as assertion → promotion
flips the inject gate. The pathology pattern in
polylogue/storage/user_write.py is your template — read it first and
mirror it (upsert_findings_as_assertions mirroring the pathology writer).

READ FIRST: bd show polylogue-rxdo.4 --json (design field = the value_json
schema spec), bd show polylogue-rxdo --json (epic context),
bd show polylogue-rxdo.9 --json (rigor-mechanisms spike — you are NOT
implementing it, but finding.v1 must not foreclose it), and
polylogue/storage/user_write.py (the pathology writer you mirror).

THE SCHEMA (finding.v1, from the bead — bead wins on conflict):
value_json schema polylogue.finding.v1:
  finding_kind: query-delta | finding-drift | measure | pathology |
                claim-vs-evidence
  statistic: {op, value, unit}
  n: int                      (denominator honesty is non-negotiable)
  query_ref, result_set_ref   (evidence refs)
  baseline/current refs       (for delta kinds)
  expected: {measure, op, value}  (OPTIONAL — this is the pre-registration
            hook: an expectation recorded BEFORE evaluation; rxdo.5's
            findings-as-tests and the rxdo.9 rigor spike build on it.
            Design the field so richer expectation shapes — bands,
            tolerances, direction-only — can be added additively.)
Defaults: status=candidate, visibility=private,
  context_policy={"inject":false,"promotion_required":true} — machine
  findings NEVER auto-inject (recursive-safety spine; a finding injected
  into agent context that then generates more findings is the loop this
  kills).
Deterministic finding id = hash(claim key + target + value + sorted
  evidence refs + detector ref) — re-materialization with identical inputs
  MUST produce zero new rows (idempotency AC).
Evidence-laundering guard: findings carry source query/result refs so a
  report renderer can warn on circular evidence ancestry.

REGISTRATION TRAPS (the real cost — the bead corrects its own corpus
design on this): adding the enum member needs NO user-tier migration
(AssertionKind column is schema-free TEXT by design). But you MUST:
  - regenerate `devtools render openapi` + `devtools render
    cli-output-schemas` (the AssertionKind enum is embedded in both);
  - add FINDING to ASSERTION_CLAIM_KINDS (find where that lives);
  - add the user_audit surface entry (the every-kind invariant in the
    user_audit test will fail without it — that failure is your friend);
  - `render all --check` exits 1 even printing per-surface "sync OK" —
    grep its output for "out of sync", never trust the tail line.

REF-FORMAT COORDINATION: the rxdo-substrate lane (running concurrently)
owns the ref grammar (query:<hash>, query-run:qr_<id>, result-set:<id>)
and the ObjectRef kind registrations; its FIRST pushed commit on
feature/fanout/rxdo-substrate is the contract. Poll for it
